rComments: Professor Bucerius is an AMAZING professor and person. I took Immigration and Crime and Crime and Neighbourhoods and I could not recommend taking her classes more. She is truly interested in teaching her students and making the classroom as relaxed as possible...she brought cookies and coffee to the midterm!

I had her for crime and immigration. She is very intelligent, approachable, and kind. She is very motherly and has become a role model for me. I love her German accent and she is very clear with her points. Out of all the professors at U OF T, she is defintely my NUMBER 1 professor. Assignments and tests were marked very fair. She is a great person
Excellent and funny prof. Crystal clear. And very easy on the eyes. I enjoyed every minute of her class!

As already noted, amazing prof (at the grad level as well!). One of the best academic experiences. Theoretical background is fantastic, practical experience is admirable and inspiring! Really approachable and down to earth.

Took her service learning class on neighbourhoods and crime and LOVED it. Lots of readings though and sometimes the readings are a bit dense but you actually learn much more in this course than in any other course in the crim program. Lots of class discussion. Prof is super funny and has lots of interesting stories to tell. Very knowledgable.
Best prof at UofT. Probably in galaxy. Very knowledgable.  Amazing research. Makes going to class fun! Expects a lot tho.
Amazing professor! She is very helpful and marks fair.

I've never had anyone that is more human than Prof. Bucerius. She's very approachable. Her assignments are hard, but that's to be expected in an advanced course. You'll learn a lot and the grades are very fair. In short: extremely cool prof - take whatever she teaches!
She is just awesome!! Clearly the best prof I've had in the past years. Very helpful, very prepared, very funny. She REALLY did research. This woman got balls!! I highly recommend her!!
